<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>Event Cancellation Notice</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        background-color: #fff3f3;
        color: #333;
        text-align: center;
        padding: 40px;
      }
      .container {
        background: #ffffff;
        padding: 30px;
        border-radius: 10px;
        box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        max-width: 600px;
        margin: auto;
      }
      h2 {
        color: #c0392b;
      }
      p {
        line-height: 1.6;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Important Update: <%= eventName %> Cancelled</h2>
      <p>We regret to inform you that <strong><%= eventName %></strong> has been cancelled due to <%= reason %>.</p>
      <p>We apologize for the inconvenience and appreciate your understanding.</p>
      <p>We’ll notify you if the event is rescheduled.</p>
      <p>— The Event Hub Team</p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>

